CatDescriptText: Mrs. Esther Austin, 171 Stueben Street, Rear, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1958, pg.2 with question: "Do people, whom you know, place more emphasis on social life than civic responsibilities?" answer reads: "In Carnegie where I used to live, they did not do too much for the youth or live up to other civic responsibilities. They went out mostly for the social life."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Esther Austin, wearing flecked coat and light colored head scarf, standing in front of light colored marble wall between store window displays of shoes and furniture
